The starlikeness and close-to-convexity of  $z\mathcal{B}_\nu$  is obtained by using Lemma \ref{lemma-ac}  in the following result.
\begin{theorem}\label{theorem-1}
For $\nu \geq 1/2$,  the normalized Bessel-Struve kernel function $z\mathcal{B}_\nu$ is starlike. The function $z\mathcal{B}_\nu$ is also close-to-convex with respect to the starlike functions $z$ and $z/(1-z)$.
\end{theorem}

It can be observed that Theorem $\ref{theorem-1}$ can also be proved by using the following lemma given in \cite{MS}.

\begin{lemma}\cite{MS}
Let $\{a_n\}_{n \geq 1}$ be a sequence of positive real number such that $a_1 \geq 2 a_2 \geq 6 a_3$ and $n(n-2)a_n \geq (n-1)(n+1)a_{n+1}$ for $n \geq 3$. Then $f(z)=z+ \sum_{n=2}^\infty a_n z^n$ is close-to-convex with respect to both the starlike functions $z$ and $z/(1-z)$. Further, the function $f$ is starlike univalent in $\mathbb{D}$.
\end{lemma}


